ia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen D Biloxham was born in 1455, in England, United Kingdom. She married Sir John de Baguley Bigelow on 7 November 1473, in Ollerton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died in July 1482, in Knutsford, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 27."},"et":{"1455–Jul 1482":"1455–juuli 1482","1452–1533":"1452–1533","1474–1540":"1474–1540","1476–Male":"1476–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1455–1482":"1455–1482","1533":"1533","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1474":"1474","1540":"1540","1452":"1452","07 Nov 1473":"7. november 1473","Jul 1482":"juuli 1482","1482":"1482","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","Ollerton, Suffolk, England, UK":"Ollerton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ollerton Hall, Cheshire, England":"Ollerton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Knutsford, Cheshire, England":"Knutsford, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1455–Jul 1482":"1455–heinäkuu 1482","1452–1533":"1452–1533","1474–1540":"147